        -:   23:// The basis cycle matrix first contains #V-#b cycles for every inner vertex (by order), then #b boundary cycles, and finally 2*g generator cycles around all handles. Total #c cycles.The cycle matrix sums information on the dual edges between the faces, and is indexed into the inner edges alone (excluding boundary)
        -:   24://input:
        -:   25://  V: #V by 3 vertices.
        -:   26://  F: #F by 3 triangles.
        -:   27://  EV: #E by 2 matrix of edges (vertex indices)
        -:   28://  EF: #E by 2 matrix of oriented adjacent faces
        -:   29://output:
        -:   30://  basisCycles:    #c by #iE basis cycles
        -:   31://  cycleCurvature:   #c by 1 curvatures of each cycle (for inner-vertex cycles, simply the Gaussian curvature.
        -:   32://  vertex2cycle:     #v by 1 map between vertex and corresponding cycle (for comfort of input from the user's side; inner vertices map to their cycles, boundary vertices to the bigger boundary cycle.
        -:   33://  innerEdges:       #iE by 1 the subset of #EV that are inner edges, and with the same ordering as the columns of basisCycles.
